  "market_context": "London session (2–5 AM EST) following Asia range; price swept the Asia range high, triggered a change in state of delivery (CISD), then 8:30 news manipulated price up into a London-formed bearish order block before continuing lower at 9:30 NY open.",
  "key_observation": "London swept the Asia range high, formed a bearish order block via a down-close candle series, and after 8:30 manipulation into that OB, price resumed lower at 9:30 with displacement.",
  "analysis_steps": [
    "Step 1: Identified the Asia session range and observed London sweeping the upper side (range high) around 04:00–05:00 EST.",
    "Step 2: Recognized the series of up-close candles that swept the high, then noted the single down-close candle closing below their opens as the change in state of delivery (CISD).",
    "Step 3: Marked the resulting bearish order block (OB) formed by that down-close candle sequence.",
    "Step 4: Observed the 8:30 economic news causing a manipulative upward move that retested and entered the London bearish OB.",
    "Step 5: Watched for continuation at key time levels (9:30 and 10:00 EST), and saw price break lower from the OB retest at 9:30 with displacement."
  ],
  "outcome": null,
  "lessons": "A valid bearish London reversal requires: (1) sweep of prior range high, (2) CISD confirmation, (3) OB formation, (4) manipulation into OB (e.g., 8:30 news), and (5) continuation lower at NY open—only then is the daily OHLC structure confirmed bearish.",
